# Heartbeats - chassis template

**This file is the chassis template.** It is NOT read by the dispatcher. At install-time, `bootstrap.sh` copies this template to `${CHASSIS_HOME}/HEARTBEATS.md` (one level above `chassis/`). The installer edits the rendered file at `${CHASSIS_HOME}/HEARTBEATS.md`, never this template.

Why: per `docs/architectural-anti-patterns.md` #17, customizations live OUTSIDE `chassis/`. The dispatcher reads `${CHASSIS_HOME}/HEARTBEATS.md`; this template ships from chassis with the schema docs only.

---

Declarative work queue for the chassis heartbeat dispatcher (`chassis/scheduled-tasks/heartbeat-dispatcher.sh`). Each `##` section defines a heartbeat: when to check, how to gather data, when to fire Claude.

> **Per LESSONS_FROM_V1.md #11:** scaffolding a heartbeat (script + prompt + state file) without registering it here means the dispatcher never invokes it. Silent dormancy. **Register every new heartbeat in this file in the same PR as the supporting scripts.**
>
> **Per #20:** the gather script is the right place for expensive checks to no-op cheaply. Every dispatcher tick (~96/day) is fine IF the gather short-circuits on trivial conditions before any paid API call.
>
> **Per #14:** validate this file's YAML blocks parse cleanly before commit. A malformed YAML block silently disables the heartbeat without erroring.

---

## Heartbeat schema

Each heartbeat is one `##` heading + a fenced ` ```yaml ` block. The dispatcher parser uses these fields:

| Field | Required | Description |
|---|---|---|
| `schedule` | yes | When to check. Formats: `every 15m`, `every 1h`, `daily 08:00`, `weekly sunday 18:00` |
| `gather` | yes | Absolute path to a shell script that emits JSON on stdout. Either `{"count": N}` for threshold conditions, or any structured JSON for `ask_model` / `always` |
| `condition` | yes | One of: `always`, `threshold <field> <op> <value>` (e.g. `threshold count > 0`), `ask_model` (requires Ollama) |
| `prompt` | yes | Path (relative to chassis root) to a markdown file Claude reads on fire |
| `model` | yes | One of: `haiku`, `sonnet`, `opus` |
| `budget` | yes | Max USD budget per `claude -p` invocation |
| `criticality` | yes | `critical` (runs in conservation mode), `normal`, `background` |
| `cwd` | no | Working directory for `claude -p` (defaults to chassis root). Useful for narrow-context subagents |
| `output_validator` | no | `true` to run the Five Failure Modes haiku check on the output |
| `condition_prompt` | no | Required when condition=ask_model. Question to send to Ollama |
| `jitter` | no | Random offset added to schedule (e.g. `30m`, `1h`). Deterministic per day+name |

---

## Format example (no real heartbeat — see commented sample below)

```yaml
schedule: every 15m
gather: ${CHASSIS_HOME}/chassis/scripts/gather-template.sh
condition: threshold count > 0
prompt: ${CHASSIS_HOME}/chassis/scheduled-tasks/example-prompt.md
model: sonnet
budget: 1
criticality: normal
```

